    "search_query": "overview of NHS Innovation Service",
    "search_results": {
      "organic": [
        {
          "title": "About the NHS Innovation Service",
          "link": "https://innovation.nhs.uk/about-the-service/",
          "snippet": "Helping you to take your healthcare innovation from idea to adoption, supporting you every step of the way.\n\nThe NHS is a large and complex system. Introducing new products and technologies can be daunting. Innovators must demonstrate the value of their healthcare product and navigate regulatory and procurement processes. For the NHS, finding new innovations that meet its needs can be equally difficult.\n\nThe NHS Innovation Service is a free, online platform created to solve both problems. It provides a centralised front door for healthcare innovations that have potential use in the NHS, matching them to relevant organisations to provide tailored support.\n\nThe NHS Innovation Service can provide support for any healthcare innovation that will impact service provision or delivery of care and could be purchased or adopted by the NHS. Innovations which fall outside of this scope may not be able to receive support via this service.",
          "position": 1
        },
        {
          "title": "Your gateway to innovation in the NHS - Innovation Service",
          "link": "https://innovation.nhs.uk/",
          "snippet": "The NHS Innovation Service offers: · Practical support for all types of healthcare innovators, from start-up to established enterprise · A centralised record of ...",
          "sitelinks": [
            {
              "title": "About the Service",
              "link": "https://innovation.nhs.uk/about-the-service/"
            },
            {
              "title": "Funding your innovation",
              "link": "https://innovation.nhs.uk/funding-your-innovation/"
            },
            {
              "title": "Innovation guide",
              "link": "https://innovation.nhs.uk/innovation-guides/"
            },
            {
              "title": "News",
              "link": "https://innovation.nhs.uk/news/"
            }
          ],
          "position": 2
        },
        {
          "title": "Innovation Service - NHS England",
          "link": "https://www.england.nhs.uk/contact-us/privacy-notice/how-we-use-your-information/public-and-partners/innovation-service/",
          "snippet": " We’ll use a cookie to save your choice. You can read more about our cookies before you choose.\n\nChange my preferencesI'm OK with analytics cookies\n\n**Your feedback matters and will make a difference.**\n\nHelp us understand your digital experience by taking our 10 minute survey. Your responses are completely anonymous.\n\nStart the survey.\n\nThe NHS Innovation Service acts as an ‘information gateway’ to support people developing new innovative products, services or initiatives in healthcare (‘innovators’), to understand processes such as the regulations and standards they will need to meet, the real-world evidence they will need to demonstrate, and NHS procurement and reimbursement processes. It will also be a single entry point for innovators to register for support and/or to apply for certain programmes.\n\nOrganisations providing support to innovators are able to communicate directly both with the innovator and with each other to help the innovator compile a single record of their progress and evidence generated to date.",
          "position": 3
        },
        {
          "title": "Innovation - NHS England",
          "link": "https://www.england.nhs.uk/ourwork/innovation/",
          "snippet": "**Your feedback matters and will make a difference.**\n\nHelp us understand your digital experience by taking our 10 minute survey. Your responses are completely anonymous.\n\nStart the survey.\n\nInnovation is critical to enabling the NHS to increase its pace and scale of change, to improve patient experience and deliver better health outcomes.\n\nThe NHS has been a leader in healthcare innovation throughout its history, revolutionising diagnostic imaging, leading cutting edge clinical research, establishing world-leading research datasets, and rolling out new technology-enabled services for patients.\n\nThe NHS’s commitment to innovation holds the key to ensuring its sustainability.\n\nNHS England is working with the Department of Health and Social Care to develop research, innovation and life sciences proposals for the 10 Year Health Plan and collaborating with the Office of Life Sciences to develop the Life Sciences Sector Industrial Strategy.",
          "position": 4
        },
        {
          "title": "NHS Innovation Service",
          "link": "https://thehealthinnovationnetwork.co.uk/about-us/supported-initiatives/nhs-innovation-service/",
          "snippet": " We will continue to work with healthcare networks and businesses to support the spread of all types of innovation within the NHS.\n\nThe NHS Innovation Service has been developed to accelerate the uptake of promising and impactful innovations into the NHS. Coordinated by the NHS Accelerated Access Collaborative (AAC), it aims to support the UK’s Life Science’s Vision to bring life-changing innovations to patients more quickly.\n\nThe online service for healthcare innovators provides support for individuals and companies at all stages of their innovation journey. It offers access to guidance and coordinated support from organisations who have experience, knowledge, and expertise in developing and supporting the widespread adoption of healthcare innovations.\n\nThe service will help healthcare innovators work with the NHS and get the support they need to get their innovation to clinicians and patients faster.",
          "position": 5
        }
      ]
    }
  }
]

